How To Install Gnome On Triaxis
Make sure you are on base with no desktop environment
Run sudo apt install gnome-session -y
then sudo apt install nautilus
then sudo apt install gnome-tweaks
if theres loginicon then change to adwaita
then sudo apt install gnome-backgrounds if you need it
then change the wallpaper or reboot or logout
sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/Triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo-text.png
Close and reopen “Settings → About”
If You Want To Remove Maxmize and Minimize Button Go To Gnome tweaks then windows then uncheck maximize and minimize
